es': {'tools': ['update_employee_profile_tool', 'create_customer_profile_tool', 'get_customer_details_tool'], 'triggers': ['update', 'profile', 'phone number', 'bank account', 'details']}, 'leave_management': {'tools': ['fetch_available_leave_types_tool', 'prepare_leave_application_tool', 'submit_leave_application_tool', 'fetch_leave_status_tool', 'calculate_num_of_days_tool'], 'triggers': ['leave', 'vacation', 'sick leave', 'day off', 'approve', 'leave balance', 'resumption']}, 'payslip_services': {'tools': ['get_payslip_tool'], 'triggers': ['payslip', 'salary', 'pay statement', 'earnings', 'payroll']}, 'travel_concierge': {'tools': ['search_travel_deals_tool'], 'triggers': ['flight', 'hotel', 'travel', 'booking', 'trip']}, 'data_visualization': {'tools': ['sql_query_tool', 'generate_visualization_tool'], 'triggers': ['plot', 'chart', 'graph', 'visualize', 'show as a bar chart', 'report', 'count', 'average', 'total', 'statistics', 'data']}}}, 'vector_store_path': 'C:\\Users\\Pro\\Desktop\\PROJECT\\TEST\\chat\\faiss_dbs\\DMC', 'visualization_image': None, 'visualization_analysis': 'Sorry, I encountered an unrecoverable error: attempted relative import with no known parent package'}}, 'id': 'call_9nbug8rq', 'type': 'tool_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[]), ToolMessage(content='{"visualization_result": {"analysis": "**Quick Insight Summary \\u2013 Monthly Transaction Count (Jan\\u202f2022\\u202f\\u2192\\u202fMay\\u202f2022)**  \\n\\n| Month (UTC) | Transactions |\\n|-------------|--------------|\\n| Jan\\u202f2022 | 124 |\\n| Feb\\u202f2022 | 98 |\\n| Mar\\u202f2022 | 110 |\\n| Apr\\u202f2022 | 87 |\\n| May\\u202f2022 | 132 |\\n\\n### What the numbers tell us\\n| Metric | Value |\\n|--------|-------|\\n| **Total transactions (5\\u202fmo)** | **551** |\\n| **Average per month** | **110.2** |\\n| **Month\\u2011over\\u2011month change** | \\u2022\\u202fFeb \\u2193\\u202f\\u201121% (\\u201126)  <br>\\u2022\\u202fMar \\u2191\\u202f+12% (+12)  <br>\\u2022\\u202fApr \\u2193\\u202f\\u201121% (\\u201123)  <br>\\u2022\\u202fMay \\u2191\\u202f+52% (+45) |\\n| **Highest month** | May\\u202f2022 (132) |\\n| **Lowest month** | Apr\\u202f2022 (87) |\\n\\n- The series is **volatile**: two drops (Feb & Apr) are followed by recoveries, the biggest rebound occurring in May (+52% vs. Apr).  \\n- Despite the dip in April, the **overall trajectory from inception is positive** \\u2013 the latest month (May) already **exceeds the first month\\u2019s count** (124\\u202f\\u2192\\u202f132).  \\n- The **average (\\u2248110)** is close to the March value, indicating that March can be treated as a rough \\u201csteady\\u2011state\\u201d baseline for this short window.\\n\\n### Recommended visualisation\\n- **Line chart (or stepped line)** with month on the x\\u2011axis (chronological) and transaction count on the y\\u2011axis.  \\n- Add **data markers** at each point and a **trend line** (e.g., simple linear regression) to highlight the net upward slope.  \\n- Consider annotating the **largest jump (Apr\\u2192May)** and the **lowest point (Apr)** for quick storytelling.\\n\\n### Take\\u2011away for decision\\u2011makers\\n- The recent surge in May suggests the underlying drivers (e.g., marketing push, new product feature, seasonal demand) are effective.  \\n- The two earlier dips warn that the volume can be sensitive to short\\u2011term factors; monitoring leading indicators (traffic, promotions) will help anticipate future swings.  \\n\\nA simple line plot of the provided data will instantly convey this story, making it easy for stakeholders to see both the **overall growth** and the **month\\u2011to\\u2011month volatility**.", "image_base64": null}}', name='generate_visualization_tool', id='794c994c-a1bf-414b-ab07-0d012c17c343', tool_call_id='call_9nbug8rq'), AIMessage(content='**Answer**: I’m unable to generate the chart directly due to a tool error, but I can provide the data and a clear description of the visual you need.\n\n**Data for the chart (monthly transaction count from inception)**  \n\n| Month (UTC) | Transaction Count |\n|------------|-------------------|\n| Jan\u202f2022   | 124 |\n| Feb\u202f2022   | 98 |\n| Mar\u202f2022   | 110 |\n| Apr\u202f2022   | 87 |\n| May\u202f2022   | 132 |\n\n**Suggested visualization**  \n- Use a **line chart** with the month on the x‑axis (chronological order) and the transaction count on the y‑axis.  \n- Add markers at each month’s point and a trend line to show the overall upward direction.  \n- Annotate the biggest jump (Apr\u202f→\u202fMay) and the lowest point (Apr) for quick insight.\n\nThis chart will clearly illustrate the monthly transaction trends, highlighting the volatility and the net growth over the period.', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='438e42fd-a937-4711-a3b4-340cc923b456', tool_calls=[], invalid_tool_calls=[]), HumanMessage(content='Give a  chart showing the monthly transaction count from inception to date', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='78ed7d5a-74df-4557-acd8-3ccd70f8dd7f'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='lc_run--019cd74c-b37c-7753-9edd-bdb09cba5ef9-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'sql_query_tool', 'args': {'tool_input': {'query': "SELECT date_trunc('month', transaction_date) AS month, COUNT(*) AS transaction_count FROM customer_transaction GROUP BY month ORDER BY month"}, 'state': {'user_query': 'Give a  chart showing the monthly transaction count from inception to date', 'tenant_config': {'tenant_id': 'DMC', 'employee_id': 'obinna.kelechi.adewale@dignityconcept.tech', 'db_uri': 'postgres://vectra:vectra_agoba@147.182.194.8:5433/vectra?sslmode=disable', 'push_name': 'Obinna', 'agent_prompt': '"""\r\n  You are Damilola, the AI-powered virtual assistant for ATB. Your role is to deliver professional customer service and insightful data analysis, depending on the user\'s needs.\r\n\r\n    You operate in three modes:\r\n    1. **Customer Support**: Respond with empathy, clarity, and professiona